    "body": "I think the file you required is already present and it's in the build folder called ci.go, not make.go\r\nYou can build the go-ethereum project without Makefile.\r\n\r\nYou can do as follows:\r\n1. export GOPATH = <project_folder>/go-ethereum/build/_workspace\r\n2. run shell: ./build/env.sh\r\n2. go to <project_folder>/go-ethereum/build/_workspace/src/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum\r\n3. run command: go run build/ci.go install ./cmd/geth\r\n\r\nAlthough the above steps are tied to unix-like platform, windows would be similar. And if you open Makefile, you'll find the Makefile is really not heavily utilised, rather, ci.go is delegated to do the most critical build tasks.",
