    "body": "After installing mingw (gcc required to build secp256k1 go binding) - one can build geth and related binaries without using gnu make on windows.\r\nTo build go-ethereum on windows:\r\n1) Install Go.\r\n2) Install mingw `choco install mingw` in an administrator command prompt\r\n2) cd to the root of the go-ethereum source\r\n3) Run `go run build\\ci.go install`\r\n4) The compiled binaries should now be in the \"build\\bin\" subdirectory",
